**Implementation in `acronym.js`:**

```javascript
export const parse = (phrase) => {
  // Replace hyphens with spaces (they're word separators)
  let processed = phrase.replace(/-/g, ' ');

  // Remove all other punctuation (keep only letters, numbers, and spaces)
  processed = processed.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9\s]/g, '');

  // Split by whitespace and filter out empty strings
  const words = processed.trim().split(/\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 0);

  // Take first letter of each word and uppercase it
  return words.map((word) => word[0].toUpperCase()).join('');
};
```

